{"COLCHICINE":[{"def":"A powerful vegetable alkaloid, C17H19NO5, extracted from the Colchicum autumnale, or meadow saffron, as a white or yellowish amorphous powder, with a harsh, bitter taste; -- called also colchicia.","pos":""}],"COLCHICUM":[{"def":"A genus of bulbous-rooted plants found in many parts of Europe, including the meadow saffron.","pos":""}],"COLCOTHAR":[{"def":"Polishing rouge; a reddish brown oxide of iron, used in polishing glass, and also as a pigment; -- called also crocus Martis.","pos":""}]}